<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-19T16:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-19T16:40:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1781</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-19T17:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I think the Department should be prepared for probable difficulty in this
                            country soon. Congress adjourned for the holidays and although due to
                            meet on the 11th has not convened as yet.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>